            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>On the inventory card, the following reading is suggested: ΛΥ in ligature and four vertical notches - numerical notation of 4. 
                This interpretation (as noted on the card) belongs to Krasotkina and Bilimovich under the supervision of I.I. Tolstoy. I agree that the
                four vertical represent number 4. What is being counted is less clear. The ligatured group of letters is more complex than ΛΥ. Alpha 
                (with left-slanted crossbar that extends beyond the left diagonal) and kappa to the right of alpha are possible alternatives, 
                but there is also an extra stroke projecting rightwards from the left end of the crossbar of alpha.
                
                The archaeological context is unknown? The object was passed to the Hermitage from the Archaeological Commission in 1904 (Record of Arch. Com. No. 5734). </p>
            </div>
